COPY public.csba_master (id, created_at, question_id, question, domain, domain_short, type, recommendation) FROM stdin;
e54bc66e-569e-4fa6-b3c7-270d6581576a	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	76590d81-ce51-4ab2-933d-d6a52b16d282	I always click on links in emails when they come from someone I know	Attack Methods	AM	Disagree	Remember to SLAM the message! Double-check the Sender, Language, Address and Message content to make sure it's legitimate. If you're not sure, then call the sender to confirm.
2cf9dcf6-34e8-4e05-837e-6f2c8c5054de	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	e3b9a690-01a2-44cb-ac70-2cad126dba8f	If an email from an unknown sender looks interesting I click on a link within it	Attack Methods	AM	Disagree	Remember to SLAM the message! Double-check the Sender, Language, Address and Message content to make sure it's legitimate. If you're not sure, then call the sender to confirm.
0d121be3-3984-4f32-ac23-4383d5252119	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	84155d8c-ebbf-46f3-be65-5eec26f348f4	I don't open email attachments if the sender is unknown to me	Attack Methods	AM	Agree	Remember to SLAM the message! Double-check the Sender, Language, Address and Message content to make sure it's legitimate. If you're not sure, then call the sender to confirm.
f7e2db60-8c6c-4220-8ce5-fb9e05b23a20	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	ad7a9008-ebe6-439f-a02c-b55c5b42e1b9	I download any files onto my work computer that will help me get the job done	Attack Methods	AM	Disagree	Downloading files without checking the sender, especially unknown senders is risky. You should only download files from senders you know and only if the files have been checked for malware and viruses.
1858f89a-d193-4b96-a812-1079b96d6363	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	950d5796-f5ae-4e65-83a8-c1cae35f3593	I assess the safety of websites before entering information	Attack Methods	AM	Agree	Be cautious when sharing information on websites. Only share necessary information. 
d9b8bcb4-c916-4453-9c7e-91c951b037d9	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	870bda19-f74d-476b-85c3-27c526ec8cfb	When browsing websites, I 'mouse-over' links to see where they go, before clicking them	Attack Methods	AM	Agree	Evaluating website links is crucial to not having your information inadvertently stolen. Always adopt caution when clickin on website links.
ed75b073-8394-45b6-993c-5b7b3da7ae30	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	2577a96c-5d10-4645-932e-17d1db4347e8	I use a different password for my social media and work accounts	Credential Management	CM	Agree	Using the same passwords across your social media and work accounts is highly risky. If any of these sites are hacked, your passwords could be available on the dark web, and worse, you're compromising your work accounts and the data those accounts may hold.
2eec685c-d6e7-4249-8a64-4c828dd60f40	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	fd776f72-a775-486e-a588-ca3e0339daa2	I share my work passwords with colleagues	Credential Management	CM	Disagree	Sharing passwords with your colleagues, while convenient, is not a good practice. What if the account is compromised? It wil be extremely difficult to determine how the compromise occurred and who might have caused it. 
6eee79a7-3cba-459a-b01f-492d225864ec	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	7b1cfdeb-16d6-4f22-9235-e0c8eb68d897	I use a combination of letters, numbers and symbols in my private (non-work) passwords	Credential Management	CM	Agree	Always use strong passwords, better yet pass phrases, comprised of letters, numbers, and symbols, for both your private and work accounts. Make sure you adhere to your work password creation policy as well. A strong passphrase is usually at least 12 characters long and include upper case, lower case, and/or special characters. In setting passwords, publicly known information, or predictable character combinations (e.g., “password”, “qwerty” or “ABC”) shall be avoided.
03355ba4-057f-4288-87e9-165193d05ddd	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	3b83c1b2-e98f-46c2-9d39-6f529991a887	When asked to change or create a password, I generally feel:	Credential Management	CM	Agree	Changing your passwords regularly, especially when asked, is a great way to reduce account compromise. Sure - it may feel irritating, but it doesn't take long, and goes a long way to keeping your accounts secure. A strong passphrase is usually at least 12 characters long and include upper case, lower case, and/or special characters. In setting passwords, publicly known information, or predictable character combinations (e.g., “password”, “qwerty” or “ABC”) shall be avoided.
3548f7b3-c0f3-4077-83f5-195dcd7acc83	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	03da853f-ee49-46d5-96b1-61c99563b0a7	I post whatever I want about my work on social media	Information Handling	IH	Disagree	The more you post in social media, whether work or private, the more potential scammers and hackers know about you, making it easier for them to spoof your identity and scamming your friends and family. When it comes to social media, the less your post, the better. 
cbca0991-3033-4f3d-a857-3649f82be1df	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	c18cc328-92e5-4f42-b15f-b2994cda6bb8	I shield or black-out information on my passport or ID-card when asked for a copy	Information Handling	IH	Agree	Your passport and IDs contain sensitive information and should only be shared if you know the person or organisation you''re sharing with. Before sharing, ask yourself why the other party is asking for that information, and how they are going to use it. And if you do share the information, it's better to encrypt the ID and share the encryption password in a separate email or chat.  
df09836c-af5e-477c-a58e-751324c1eb67	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	bd24c2f1-2d38-4b6d-b5b0-7dfebc4df7ca	In the past I have left sensitive information unattended	Information Handling	IH	Disagree	You should never leave sensititve information unattended on your desk or in any public location, even for a minute. Always lock the information in a drawer or cabinet, or if in a public place, take the information with you. 
1fa3c04e-0b7d-49ed-9f14-fa4df64a24f6	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	4252b7da-b41a-4fc8-8ab8-d2cbc11d89cc	I have sent potentially sensitive information via e-mail without encryption	Information Handling	IH	Disagree	Always encrypt senstive information before sending. And share the password with the recipient separately. That way, even if the email gets into the wrong hands, it can't be decrypted and will still be safe.
0131dcf2-6605-482b-b554-e0a38f28ee11	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	bb71833f-e8e4-4972-8448-112680fc2ae4	If I noticed a security incident, I would report it	Incident Response	IR	Agree	Always report any security incidents you see through the proper channels, even if you think they are minor. You never know if a minor incident could escalate to something major. Protect yourself and your colleagues!
3ac078b3-2c87-4025-bbf9-ed5ea40b6ef0	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	dc5ed220-c06b-412c-bf57-f9b94b64e000	If I noticed a security incident I wouldn'’t know who to report it to	Incident Response	IR	Disagree	Knowing where to report security incidents is important to ensure the your organisations general safety. Please contact your manager or your IT department if you're not sure where to go.
493c8ee9-a789-433a-8d14-158d41813002	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	4ac189ce-4c04-43d9-a07a-a35188c48b89	When I receive a suspicious mail on my private e-mail account I am confident about what to do	Incident Response	IR	Agree	Remember to SLAM the message! Double-check the Sender, Language, Address and Message content to make sure it's legitimate. If you're not sure, then call the sender to confirm.
e8065780-c8a6-470d-b78c-90bb299365d5	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	c46658cf-894a-47cb-9ef0-f1c75f15f87d	When I receive a suspicious mail on my work e-mail account I am confident about what to do	Incident Response	IR	Agree	Remember to SLAM the message! Double-check the Sender, Language, Address and Message content to make sure it's legitimate. If you're not sure what to do with the email, check with your IT department or your management.
ba9fe047-1a5c-431d-9844-2ee3fb0c7cbe	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	7a25310b-cba3-4db8-be14-2cd6edb40321	When working in a public place, I leave my laptop unattended	Physical Security / Situational Awareness	SA	Disagree	Never leve your laptop unattended in a public place, even if the place is crowded. You cannot  rely on the people around you to stop a stranger from taking your laptop. And if you lose your laptop, you lose the data on the laptop and who knows what would happen then!
3242095d-7c64-450c-8d23-d5c6e9faaba9	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	d4ab1d25-1b7e-4bed-a313-81b4bbd312f6	In a public space I check that strangers can't see my laptop screen	Physical Security / Situational Awareness	SA	Agree	It's good practice to now allow strangers, no matter how innocuous the work you're doing and how innocent they may look. People are generally nosy and you never know who those prying eyes belong to and what they can learn about you or your organisation from the work you are doing.
88b81d6f-f55a-4cd0-abf8-ae51b66f080d	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	b1a89a78-34ce-468c-816e-2403b9bf065d	When sensitive print-outs need to be disposed of, I throw them away at the office or I ensure that they are shredded or destroyed	Physical Security / Situational Awareness	SA	Agree	While throwing away sensitive print-outs in the office may seem like a safe choice, it's one of the ways hackers and scammers use to pay someone to collect the trash for them. It's always safer, even in the office, to 
23b1b520-5e9d-452b-9855-527d108bd2df	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	e46e42b1-827c-4b75-a9fe-b0856e27cb27	If I noticed my colleague ignoring security rules, I wouldn't take any action	Physical Security / Situational Awareness	SA	Disagree	You should gently remind your colleague about your organisation's security rules and policies. If you're not comfortable doing that, you should report it to your manager or IT department. 
b83ff1b1-6d6a-4484-b482-ccf14f12d94e	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	8110d577-d133-4328-a4f5-6b92e2472113	When I notice a new face in a restricted office space, I take action to find out if this person's presence is legitimate	Physical Security / Situational Awareness	SA	Agree	If you notice a new face or stranger in your office, you should always walk up to them, introduce yourself and ask how you could help them. That's the easiest way to ascertain if they are legitimate or not. If you feel they are not legit, then report that immediately to your security or management.
3c959180-87af-4182-9a94-2281a348db86	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	05557b4d-418e-45d6-8a2b-09084fe70269	At home I (or someone in my household) have adjusted the security of my internet connection	Secure Usage	SU	Agree	Leaving the default settings on your home internet connection, especially the admin passwords of the router, is the surest way leave your internet connection vulnerable to outside abuse. You should change the default SSID and password as quickly as possible, and if you don't know how, you should contact your internet provider or a trusted person to help you change that.
a2ca7bac-eaab-488c-bd5b-3252c89ef851	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	8df13a9e-03ce-4009-808b-424d310f2a29	I lock my computer when I leave it unattended	Secure Usage	SU	Agree	Firstly - you shouldn't leave your computer unattended in a public environment. Always take it with you. Second - if you have to leave it unattended in a work environment, no matter the work you do and how much you trust your colleagues, always lock your computer so no one can access your computer and compromise it in any way.
ea1016e4-a02e-41b6-8180-a0c0bd96eb36	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	ee11edb1-ac90-425e-a2bd-43040866ba7a	When I'm in a public place I use free WiFi if it is available	Secure Usage	SU	Disagree	Remember to be careful with public WiFi.  They are magnets for criminals.  Minimise your use, use a VPN or your phone’s hotspot.
f5858293-23a9-431d-8652-0e98642ee89d	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	85095226-bbe1-4d7d-8363-ade3a0b16780	When I use public WiFi I use a VPN service	Secure Usage	SU	Agree	Remember to be careful with public WiFi.  They are magnets for criminals.  Minimise your use, use a VPN or your phone’s hotspot.
bdacc714-26f5-478a-ae5f-fd2271a0bcec	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	9c82b215-a319-4554-bd2d-1b31ba03cebf	I've used my private e-mail address for work related matters in the past	Secure Usage	SU	Disagree	\N
5ea25bf7-ecf0-4272-a5c7-a28309e19870	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	bb094b54-b42d-41f5-96c8-01040e9f02a1	I don't regularly review my social media privacy settings	Target Awareness	TA	Disagree	Criminals can learn a lot about you from your social media, and can target those who follow you. Securing your social media privacy settings are important to safeguarding your identity and of those around you. 
422ec2b2-2351-4daa-bdbc-c139737d168e	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	71558214-17ae-4205-9476-f25421b5d08c	I don'’t worry about what I post on social media	Target Awareness	TA	Disagree	The more you post in social media, whether work or private, the more potential scammers and hackers know about you, making it easier for them to spoof your identity and scamming your friends and family. When it comes to social media, the less your post, the better. 
1cce0d1d-9ca6-4d36-91de-916c3baa8af4	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	e3b4b0df-2ea6-427b-8649-afa1daf6377d	I believe that I am a potential target for cyber-crime	Target Awareness	TA	Agree	The attacker may not be after your money or data but that you are a channel to the organisation's systems and data. 
5551ca0d-756c-48cf-bbf9-150c2b9fde98	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	f4cb7b69-cb34-49e2-bffd-e00981429fe1	When receiving e-mails, I have checked things like:  sender's address, where do links lead to, did I expect this mail, etc	Target Awareness	TA	Agree	Remember to SLAM the message! Double-check the Sender, Language, Address and Message content to make sure it's legitimate. If you're not sure, then call the sender to confirm.
d7cc90f1-60ad-448a-ac66-a566441f178d	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	c351910c-bd03-4539-993f-c8f4925713e0	Compared to your family, friends and colleagues, how do you rate your own security behaviour?	Statistics	ZS	\N	\N
6089916b-70cd-4bcc-bd6a-4edd3c94743f	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	61f58c04-88c4-4379-9aaf-2dc8a48a456d	How secure do you think your colleagues act in general	Statistics	ZS	\N	\N
6f09e0eb-46fb-4563-b5d9-dde5eb33e2b3	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	e8966dab-91c5-4286-a25c-3db6966c20da	How well protected do you think your company is against cyber-crime?	Statistics	ZS	\N	\N
ab13bdba-59dd-4072-bf7b-50d0e899acd2	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	03265d81-ff08-4439-a921-b26074fd5ee0	Have you ever been the victim of cyber-crime?	Profile	ZZ	\N	\N
0c830444-2ed2-493d-aaf7-1cf66c6f23d8	2025-07-11 23:21:45.728701+00	512d96e4-1504-4d7f-982f-3e291caf3d27	Do you work in a job directly related to Information Security, Cyber security or Anti-Fraud?	Profile	ZZ	\N	\N
