e762e53a-7a9e-4ccb-b65b-039514c66273	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	[6]  CYBERSECURITY: Asset - People - Equip staff with cyber-hygiene practices as the first line of defence	40	Healthcare providers shall ensure employees attend cybersecurity awareness\ntraining periodically so that they are aware of the security practices and behaviour expected of them. This requirement may be met in different ways, e.g., through regular internal training of staff on the healthcare provider�s cyber and data security policies and practices, employees going through selflearning\ncybersecurity resource materials, engaging external training providers, or\nconducting simulated phishing exercises for staff.	No		No		Sample Accepable Use of Technology Resources Policy	2025-05-28 22:06:20.840295+00	2025-05-28 22:06:20.840295+00	6	1. Organisation shall ensure personnel (i.e., full time / part time staff, interns, contractors, vendors) who have access to the organisation�s network/systems are briefed and trained on cybersecurity awareness.\n2. The cybersecurity training shall minimally include Cyber & Data good practices via self-learning, external training provider or internal training.\n3. Organisation shall document the frequency of the training and maintain records of the briefings and trainings attended by staff.
c2751725-358d-4c2f-ae10-fcb5e1aac727	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	[6]  CYBERSECURITY: Asset - People - Equip staff with cyber-hygiene practices as the first line of defence	41	Cyber hygiene practices and guidelines shall be developed for employees to adopt in their daily operations, to ensure that they are aware of the security practices and behaviours expected of them. For example, the cyber hygiene practices and guidelines should include the following topics to mitigate incidents arising from the human factor.\nTable 2 lists examples of measures that can be considered for developing cyber hygiene practices and guidelines:\ni. Protect yourself from phishing;\nii. Set strong passphrase as passwords;\niii. Protect your corporate and/or personal devices (used for work);\niv. Report cyber incidents;\nv. Handle and disclose businesscritical data carefully; and\nvi. Work onsite and remotely in a secure manner	No		No		Sample Security Awareness & Training Policy	2025-05-28 22:06:20.840295+00	2025-05-28 22:06:20.840295+00	6	The cybersecurity awareness program shall at minimum include topics, such as:\na) phishing awareness and impact,\nb) use of strong passphrase,\nc) BYOD usage,\nd) reporting of suspicious activities or incident,\ne) managing sensitive data.\nf) risks of using public WiFi\nExamples of implementing cybersecurity awareness can be:\n- Screen savers\n- Email bulletins\n- Posters
