26721096-1855-4d0b-835b-46025a7b4c3f	Quiz!	It's Quiz Time!  After 10 episodes, it's a good time to do a little quiz and see what you remember.  It'll help you and us be safe and cyber secure.  And of course, it's important for our clients and stakeholders.  It won't take more than 10 minutes!	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	draft	\N	\N	\N	lesson	\N
ba58297d-d2cd-4f36-a80c-a0dcacb897de	Personal Data and You. Can you handle it? 	We all deal with people's personal data these days:  clients, colleagues, customers, voters, you name it.  We have to be careful.  Why did one company get fined over 850 million dollars?  Or a mayor gets fined 2 grand? It can be tricky:  what can we do, what can't we do, what do we have to do?  Let's take a look.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-08-30 20:04:23.885184+00	published	node_1756415301542	10	\N	lesson	\N
e8258a38-0f83-4d7d-967e-de642737e1cb	Overarching Obligations	The PDPA seems daunting but don't worry: this lesson explains your overarching obligations with regards to the act and walks you through critical terms you need to know, and sets the foundation of your knowledge of the PDPA.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-08-31 07:13:36.470285+00	draft	node_1756586512109	10	\N	lesson	\N
57cde5ae-57f4-4a5d-a956-2368d7f851b8	HIB and Cybersecurity	This lesson covers what you need to know about cybersecurity in relation to HIB.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-09-11 05:37:49.273498+00	2025-09-11 05:37:49.273498+00	published	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N
fc018c58-7bf8-4b54-ae01-79501989164a	Retention Limit	Cease retention of personal data or dispose of it in a proper manner when it is no longer needed for any business or legal purpose.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-08-25 17:03:17.37634+00	draft	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N
207c4b5f-11b3-40e9-b062-103d1dae1263	Transfer Limitation	Transfer personal data to another country only according to the requirements prescribed under the regulations, to ensure that the standard of protection is comparable to the protection under the PDPA, unless exempted by the PDPC.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-08-25 17:04:00.401198+00	published	node_1754256700672	10	\N	lesson	\N
84771ac6-e44a-4e3a-9bc0-acc0ccd6b4c8	Access and Correction	Upon request, organisations have to provide individuals with access to their personal data as well as information about how the data was used or disclosed within a year before the request.\n\nOrganisations are also required to correct any error or omission in an individual’s personal data as soon as practicable and send the corrected data to other organisations to which the personal data was disclosed (or to selected organisations that the individual has consented to), within a year before the correction is made. 	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-08-25 17:04:40.253381+00	draft	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N
696f4cfb-488c-4638-b33f-3f55fb10a822	HIB for Nursing Staff	Simplified lesson covering key HIB knowledge for Nursing Staff	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-09-11 05:41:21.957508+00	2025-09-12 01:14:20.012241+00	published	node_1757595841713	10	\N	lesson	\N
eccf0a0c-fb9e-47af-a9f8-2a0adeb9bd32	HIB for Nursing Staff - 2	This lesson focusses on managing passwords.	990a457c-eb6f-4202-8df6-f2c098c1b50c	2025-09-12 01:19:25.24387+00	2025-09-17 06:08:36.163772+00	published	node_1757640044013	10	\N	lesson	\N
09e15c67-cd0e-42cf-b68a-69541984f7b7	Notification	Notify individuals of the purposes for which your organisation is intending to collect, use or disclose their personal data.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-08-25 16:59:29.737949+00	published	node_1754350416199	10	\N	lesson	\N
b9430ff6-c590-40a4-b620-ae26595b43be	Consent	Only collect, use or disclose personal data for purposes which an individual has given his/her consent to.\n\nAllow the individual to withdraw consent, with reasonable notice, and inform him/her of the likely consequences of withdrawal. Once consent is withdrawn, make sure that you cease to collect, use or disclose the individual’s personal data.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-08-25 16:59:55.564956+00	published	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N
4305695a-8ebb-4fe4-b79d-00389314cf20	My First Quiz		56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-09-20 05:15:52.564245+00	2025-10-08 04:07:01.709504+00	published	node_1758345357336	10	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	quiz	{"max_attempts": 10, "retry_policy": "limited", "trophy_config": {"trophy_name": "", "award_trophy": true, "trophy_description": ""}, "certificate_config": {"issuer": "Learning Platform", "certificate_name": "", "expires_after_days": null, "generate_certificate": true}, "passing_percentage": 70, "time_limit_minutes": null, "show_score_during_quiz": true}
2b6a20d5-06af-4296-a0e6-3f859f399ea7	Simple mini node lesson	For generic testing purposes, including language translations.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-08-17 03:37:59.728912+00	2025-09-03 17:27:47.540956+00	published	node_1755401924746	2	\N	lesson	\N
0d13dd7b-8552-4cfc-b24c-570faddede34	Data Breach Notification	In the event of a data breach, organisations must take steps to assess if it is notifiable. If the data breach likely results in significant harm to individuals, and/or are of significant scale, organisations are required to notify the PDPC and the affected individuals as soon as practicable.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-08-25 17:05:20.220823+00	2025-08-25 17:05:20.220823+00	draft	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N
6e05305d-f774-4d57-bcb5-09be7800e062	Accuracy Obligation	Make reasonable effort to ensure that the personal data collected is accurate and complete, especially if it is likely to be used to make a decision that affects the individual or to be disclosed to another organisation.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-10-28 15:11:52.982711+00	published	\N	10	990a457c-eb6f-4202-8df6-f2c098c1b50c	lesson	\N
76255dc9-84b9-4d63-b725-eb72136128f9	Accountability	The Accountability Obligation is an overarching responsibility that the organisation and each indvividual undertakes to protect the personal data that it has or is in control of. 	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-10-28 15:14:08.287216+00	published	node_1756625381826	5	990a457c-eb6f-4202-8df6-f2c098c1b50c	lesson	\N
1cda6a5b-6a8c-4556-b121-0e1eb4edac74	Protection	Reasonable security arrangements have to be made to protect the personal data in your organisation’s possession to prevent unauthorised access, collection, use, disclosure or similar risks.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-10-28 15:14:27.196991+00	published	\N	10	990a457c-eb6f-4202-8df6-f2c098c1b50c	lesson	\N
19ba4be0-819c-4065-a3dd-7729d6c53485	Data Portability	At the request of the individual, organisations are required to transmit the individual’s data that is in the organisation’s possession or under its control, to another organisation in a commonly used machine-readable format. \n\nExceptions may apply to the obligations above. For more information, please refer to Advisory Guidelines on Key Concepts in the Personal Data Protection Act.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-08-25 17:06:59.287186+00	2025-08-25 17:06:59.287186+00	draft	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N
a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890	Introduction to the Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA)	Interactive data protection training focusing on creating a strong understanding of personal data, and how to protect and handle it.	\N	2025-07-09 18:02:16.051722+00	2025-08-28 21:05:44.625544+00	published	intro	10	\N	lesson	\N
af3d4820-1e57-4501-89f8-305aa9e7b9e9	HIB and Data Protection	This lesson covers what you need to know about data protection in relation to HIB.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-09-11 05:38:07.870877+00	2025-09-11 05:40:11.500715+00	draft	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N
ad4e3c99-975a-427a-b680-03b774ec4317	Passphrase Best Practices	We all use passwords and know about using mixed cases, numbers, special characters, etc. when we create passwords. But are they really safe? This lesson covers the best practices of creating passwords that are secure, and not easily hackable. 	\N	2025-08-08 15:27:59.879887+00	2025-10-28 15:10:33.798259+00	published	node_1754667499326	4	990a457c-eb6f-4202-8df6-f2c098c1b50c	lesson	\N
